   - A static variable is a variable that retains its value between function calls. It is initialized only once when the program starts.
   - When a static variable is used within a function, it belongs to the function, not to the instance of the class.
   - Static variables are shared by all instances of a class.

   Example:
   ```csharp
public class MyClass {
    public static int myStaticVariable = 10;

    public void myMethod() {
        myStaticVariable = 20;
    }
}
